                  "author": "Warden's Echo",
                  "pages": [
                    [
                      {
                        "text": "They sealed the portal, buried the city, and left only the Warden to remember. But memory is a kind of Dream, and the Warden dreams endlessly.",
                        "color": "dark_gray",
                        "italic": true
                      }
                    ],
                    [
                      {
                        "text": "The sealing was not a decision \u2014 it was a panic. They collapsed tunnels, flooded corridors, buried the city under miles of stone. They destroyed every map, every record, every reference to the portal's location.",
                        "color": "dark_gray",
                        "italic": true
                      }
                    ],
                    [
                      {
                        "text": "But they could not destroy the Warden. The Warden was the seal itself. To destroy it would be to open the lock.",
                        "color": "dark_gray",
                        "italic": true
                      }
                    ],
                    [
                      {
                        "text": "\n\n  ",
                        "color": "white"
                      },
